summary: An ordinance appropriating the sum of Two Hundred ($200.00) Dollars out of the general fund to pay the claim of Levi Saylor for damages done to house owned by claimant located at 1318 Alki Avenue, Seattle, said damages being occasioned by the breaking of a sewer pipe located on 45th Avenue Southwest, adjacent to said premises, which flooded said premises with mud and debris on or about the 10th day of February 1916, and authorizing the drawing of a warrant therefor.
